\begin_layout Description
2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Proof:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $A\in\mathbb{C}^{m\times n}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $b\in\mathbb{C}^{m}$
\end_inset

, so 
\begin_inset Formula $b\notin range(A)$
\end_inset

, thus this rectangular system of equations is overdetermined.
 Denote 
\begin_inset Formula $r=b-Ax$
\end_inset

 called the residual, then by Theorem 11.1 a vector 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 minimizes the residual norm 
\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
\uuline off
\uwave off
\noun off
\color none

\begin_inset Formula $||r||_{2}=||b-Ax||_{2}$
\end_inset

 if and only if 
\begin_inset Formula $r\perp range(A)$
\end_inset

, that is 
\begin_inset Formula $A^{*}r=0$
\end_inset

.
 
\family default
\series default
\shape default
\size default
\emph default
\bar default
\strikeout default
\uuline default
\uwave default
\noun default
\color inherit
Thus 
\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
\uuline off
\uwave off
\noun off
\color none

\begin_inset Formula $A^{*}r=0\,\Leftrightarrow\, A^{*}Ax=A^{*}b$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let's compute 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 now.
 In proof of 
\series bold
problem 6.3 
\series default
(see above), we have already proved that if 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 has full rank, then 
\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
\uuline off
\uwave off
\noun off
\color none

\begin_inset Formula $A^{*}A$
\end_inset

 is nonsingular, thus 
\begin_inset Formula $A^{*}A$
\end_inset

 's inverse exits.
 By the given reduced SVD of 
\begin_inset Formula $A=\hat{U}\hat{\Sigma}\hat{V}^{*}$
\end_inset

, then we find 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
x=(A^{*}A)^{-1}A^{*}b=(\hat{V}\Sigma\hat{U}^{*}\hat{U}\hat{\Sigma}\hat{V}^{*})^{-1}(\hat{U}\hat{\Sigma}\hat{V}^{*})^{*}b=\hat{V}\Sigma^{-2}\hat{V}^{*}\hat{V}\Sigma\hat{U}^{*}b=\hat{V}\Sigma^{-1}\hat{U}^{*}b
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
thus
\end_layout

